        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The principle of the sensitivity enhancing structure shown as follows: When the parallel plate capacitors  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "(C_{ESP})"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " are applied to the same bias voltage  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "(V_{BP})"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " and the displacement of proof mass  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "(x_{mass})"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " is much smaller than the gap of the parallel plate actuators  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "(g_{ESP})"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the net electrostatic force on the proof-mass is cancelled out in the first order, but the effect of the spring softening is doubled. The reduced effective spring stiffness on sensitive axis results in that the acceleration induced inertial force can be more effectively transmit to the resonator to enhance the sensitivity  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "(S_{ES})"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". When  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "g_{ESP} >> x_{mass}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " and the amplification ratio of micro-levers is a constant with the range of the input of acceleration, the  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S_{ES}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " can be derived as (1): "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                66,
                246,
                486,
                435
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "S _ {E S} = \\frac {\\partial \\omega_ {T}}{\\partial A _ {c c}} \\approx S _ {0} \\frac {1}{1 - k _ {e} / k _ {e f f}} \\tag {1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/a75eaa6173ce44cce2d6e9dd5230e64611072414df0a2f894218bffbaa59dec5.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
