        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "III. EXPERIMENTAL RESULTS "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                174,
                66,
                372,
                80
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The prototype device was fabricated using a SOI foundry process and vacuum pakaged in wafer-level, then mounted on a 24-pin DIP ceramic chip carrier (see Figure 1(b)). To calibrate the sensitivity of the prototype accelerometer, tilt table is used to apply  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "+/-1\\mathrm{g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " load on the device. The different voltages apply to the four pairs of symmetrical parallel plate capacitors and the resonant frequencies are characterised using network analyser (Keysight E5061B) with a transimpedance amplifier, as shown in Fig.4. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                66,
                85,
                486,
                212
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The results of the measurement are shown in the Figure 5, presents the resonant frequencies shift with input acceleration vary from  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "-1\\mathrm{g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " to  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "+1\\mathrm{g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". The sensitivity variance with different voltages is derived from the open-loop test results (see Figure 5 inset). The original sensitivity of the accelerometer  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "(V_{BP} = 0\\mathrm{V})"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " is about  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "444\\mathrm{Hz / g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". When the  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V_{BP}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " applied to the back-to-back parallel plate capacitors, the sensitivity of accelerometer is increased. For  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V_{BP} = 50\\mathrm{V}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " applied on the actuator, the sensitivity is  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "691\\mathrm{Hz / g}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " boosted up  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "60\\%"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": " higher than the original sensitivity and the nonlinearity is  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0.6\\%"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", meanwhile, the original nonlinearity is  "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0.4\\%"
